*** GAMS/LINDO option file for ReEDS
*** Docs: https://www.gams.com/latest/docs/S_LINDO.html
*** Activate with: model.OptFile = 1;
***
*** LINDO API uses all-caps parameter names (LS_ / SPLEX_ / SOLVER_ / SOLVERIPM_).
*** It auto-detects problem class, so submitting ReEDS with "option LP = LINDO"
*** is sufficient - LINDO will dispatch its LP solver.

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Algorithm selection - barrier with crossover, matching the CPLEX baseline
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** LP method: 1 free (auto), 2 primal simplex, 3 dual simplex,
***            4 barrier (no crossover), 5 barrier + crossover, 6 concurrent
*** Use 5 (barrier + crossover) for ReEDS to get the basic solution downstream code expects.
*** Selects the LP method. Note: integer code as shown above.
LS_IPARAM_SOL_TYPE_LP 5

*** Dual simplex strategy: 1 single-phase, 2 two-phase
SPLEX_DUAL_PHASE 1

*** Run barrier and simplex concurrently if at least 2 threads are available.
*** 0 off, 1 on if >= 2 threads, 2 always concurrent
SOLVER_CONCURRENT_OPTMODE 1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Parallelism (matches CPLEX baseline of 8 threads)
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LS_IPARAM_NUM_THREADS 8

*** Use threads aggressively in MIP / sub-solves (irrelevant for pure LP, but harmless)
LS_IPARAM_MIP_PARA_FLAG 1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Time / iteration limits
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** LP time limit in seconds (-1 = no limit). 2 days matches cplex.opt.
LS_DPARAM_SOLVER_TIMLMT 172800

*** Global LP iteration limit (-1 = no limit)
LS_IPARAM_LP_ITRLMT -1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Tolerances - matched to ReEDS cplex.opt where possible
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Primal feasibility tolerance (CPLEX eprhs 1e-5)
LS_DPARAM_SOLVER_FEASTOL 1e-5

*** Dual feasibility / optimality tolerance (CPLEX epopt 1e-6)
LS_DPARAM_SOLVER_OPTTOL 1e-6

*** Barrier convergence tolerance (CPLEX barepcomp 1e-8)
LS_DPARAM_SOLVERIPM_TOL_OPT 1e-8

*** Pivot tolerance
LS_DPARAM_SOLVER_PIVTOL 1e-7

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Crossover (barrier -> basic solution)
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Run crossover after barrier. ReEDS needs basic marginals downstream.
*** 0 off, 1 on
LS_IPARAM_SOLVER_DO_BASIS_CROSSOVER 1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Pre-processing / scaling
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Presolve level: 0 off, > 0 enables presolve (default is auto)
LS_IPARAM_SOLVER_PRE_LP -1

*** Scaling: 0 off, > 0 progressively stronger scaling
LS_IPARAM_SOLVER_IUSOL 1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Warm start
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** 1 = use any basis already in memory (warm start), 0 = cold start.
*** ReEDS sequentially advances years, so warm-starting between SOLVEs is helpful
*** when feasible.
LS_IPARAM_SOL_USE_BASIS 1

*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Output
*** ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*** Verbosity 0 quiet, ..., 4 maximum
LS_IPARAM_SOLVER_OUTPUT_LEVEL 3

threads = 8